## Infra utilities over language primitives

When the infrastructure provides a utility, **always** use it — never substitute with language primitives or one-off helper functions:

| Operation | Use | Not |
|-----------|-----|-----|
| Deep object merge | `merge()` from `@nu-art/ts-common` | Spread operator (`{...defaults, ...overrides}`) for nested objects |
| URL composition | `composeUrl()` from `@nu-art/ts-common` | Manual string concatenation |
| Query params | `composeQueryParams()` from `@nu-art/ts-common` | Hand-built query strings |

The infra utilities handle edge cases and maintain consistency. Reaching for raw language features is a code smell that you missed an existing capability.
